<BaseLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy - BusinessClaw" 
  description="Privacy policy for BusinessClaw productivity automation OAuth application"
>
  <ContentLayout>
    <PageHeader
      title="Privacy Policy"
      subtitle="BusinessClaw"
      description="Privacy policy for personalized productivity automation"
    />

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/70"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> February 18, 2026</p>

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          This privacy policy describes how BusinessClaw ("the App") accesses and handles 
          Google account data. This is a personal productivity automation application.
        </p>

        <h2>Who This Applies To</h2>
        <p>
          This application is for <strong>personal use</strong> to provide personalized and 
          opinionated productivity automation. It is not a commercial service available to the 
          general public.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Access</h2>
        <p>The App requests access to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Gmail</strong> - To read, send, and manage emails</li>
          <li><strong>Google Calendar</strong> - To view and create calendar events</li>
          <li><strong>Google Drive</strong> - To search and access files</li>
          <li><strong>Google Contacts</strong> - To view contact information</li>
          <li><strong>Google Sheets</strong> - To read and update spreadsheet data</li>
          <li><strong>Google Docs</strong> - To read document content</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How Data Is Used</h2>
        <p>All data accessed through this App is used solely for personal productivity automation, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Reading and responding to emails with intelligent automation</li>
          <li>Managing calendar events and schedules</li>
          <li>Searching and organizing files</li>
          <li>Accessing contact information for communications</li>
          <li>Working with spreadsheets and documents</li>
          <li>Automating routine business and personal tasks</li>
          <li>Providing personalized productivity insights and recommendations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Storage and Sharing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Storage:</strong> OAuth tokens are stored locally on authorized devices</li>
          <li><strong>Third-party sharing:</strong> Your data is <strong>never</strong> shared with third parties</li>
          <li><strong>Commercial use:</strong> This app is not used for any commercial purposes</li>
          <li><strong>Data retention:</strong> Data is only accessed when needed and is not permanently stored by the App</li>
          <li><strong>Processing:</strong> All data processing happens locally on your authorized devices</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Google API Services</h2>
        <p>
          This App's use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the 
          <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Google API Services User Data Policy
          </a>, including the Limited Use requirements.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>OAuth credentials are stored securely on authorized devices</li>
          <li>All communication with Google APIs uses encrypted HTTPS connections</li>
          <li>No authentication data is logged or transmitted to external services</li>
          <li>Access tokens are managed with industry-standard security practices</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Control</h2>
        <p>
          You can revoke the App's access to your Google account at any time by visiting:<br>
          <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Google Account Permissions
          </a>
        </p>

        <h2>Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>This policy may be updated occasionally. Changes will be reflected with a new "Last Updated" date.</p>

